@dvassallo I also completed my 2025 taxes with Claude. S-Corp, multiple streams of income, real estate, international properties, payroll, and a lot of complexity.

It took time but Claude was clutch. 

Best part: I learned a ton about tax law over a week working on this.

@MichaelMindrum I blacked out all personal information before giving it to the model. There are things I'm sure still went through (like my company name), but at least most of the sensitive info didn't make it to the model.

I know this is a risk. I'd rather not share any of this with the model, but I don't think the risk is greater than sharing it with a big CPA firm.

It all comes down to a tradeoff. The only way to be safe is to do everything yourself with no external help.

@LoganGrafTax The first time I used a CPA (a large corpo, not a single person), they were extremely efficient and extremely wrong.

Everybody I know that has used a CPA or a tax preparer hates it.

Biggest complaint: they are usually good at doing the common stuff, but underprepared for the uncommon situations. They cut a ton of corners and you’ll never know.

